{
  "texts": [
    "In FELLAS, the set size is set to 1 for efficiency.",
    "As a result, the final local training objective for each client is changed to:L = L 𝑟𝑒𝑐 + 𝛼 L 𝑐𝑙(10)where 𝛼 controls the contributions of contrastive enhancement.",
    "Interacted Item Inference AttacksIn FELLAS, clients send sequences to an external LLM server, raising additional privacy concerns compared to vanilla FedSeqRec.",
    "Although the sequences are perturbed with 𝑑 X -privacy guarantees, to fully address users' privacy concerns, we further design two inference attacks based on users' uploaded noisy sequences to verify the empirical privacy risks of data leakage.",
    "As illustrated in Figure 3, these two attacks are launched in the most practical adversarial settings: (1) the external LLM server acting as a curious-but-honest server, and (2) both the LLM server and the central server being curious-but-honest and cooperating maliciously."
  ]
}